  "response": "Here are some common examples of imperative sentences:\n\n1. Commands:\n- \"Stop talking!\"\n- \"Be quiet.\"\n- \"Listen carefully.\"\n\n2. Requests:\n- \"Please help me.\"\n- \"Can you open the door?\"\n- \"Pass the salt.\"\n\n3. Instructions:\n- \"Mix the ingredients.\"\n- \"Turn left at the next street.\"\n- \"Read the instructions first.\"\n\n4. Advice:\n- \"Take care of yourself.\"\n- \"Study hard.\"\n- \"Eat your vegetables.\"\n\n5. Suggestions:\n- \"Try this dessert.\"\n- \"Let's go to the movies.\"\n- \"Consider my advice.\"\n\n6. Warnings:\n- \"Watch out!\"\n- \"Don't touch that.\"\n- \"Be careful.\"\n\n7. Everyday Directions:\n- \"Come here.\"\n- \"Sit down.\"\n- \"Close the door.\"\n\n8. Cooking Instructions:\n- \"Preheat the oven.\"\n- \"Stir the sauce.\"\n- \"Add salt to taste.\"\n\nThese sentences typically start with a verb and often imply a direct action or instruction to the listener.",
